1242.name: ER 90 S-G (P92) Tig
1242.Applications: TIG/GTAW wire for high temperature, creep resistant, modified 9%Cr1%Mo martensitic steel (T92/P92).  Alloy T92/P92 is widely used in the power generating industry for fossil fuel ultra-super-critical (USC) power plant boilers and turbines; the alloy is also finding applications in the chemical and oil and gas industries.
1242.Suitable_For: For matching P92, 9%Cr1.7%W0.5%Mo, creep resisting martensitic steels. X10CrWMoVNb 9 2, ASTM: A182 grade F92, A213 grade T92, A335 grade P92, A387 grade 92
